<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued October 13 at 12:24AM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 100 AM CDT
FOR NORTHERN PICKENS...SOUTHWESTERN FAYETTE AND SOUTHEASTERN LAMAR
COUNTIES...
At 1224 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Kennedy to near Millport to near Ethelsville,
moving southeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Fayette, Gordo, Reform, Millport, Kennedy, Belk, Ethelsville,
Ashcraft Corner, Cody, North Pickens Airport, McShan, Shaw, Lubbub,
Hightogy, Macedonia, Forest and Owens.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
